olive oil
1 carrot
1 potato
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 packet Beef Rump
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet mayonnaise
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Cut carrot and potato into fries.
• Place veggie fries on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 30-35 minutes.
• Meanwhile, roughly chop tomato and cucumber.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• When the fries have 10 minutes cook time remaining, place beef rump between two sheets of baking paper. Pound beef with a meat mallet or rolling pin until slightly flattened. Season beef with salt and pepper.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a high heat. When oil is hot, cook beef, turning, for 5-6 minutes (depending on thickness), or until cooked to your liking. In the last minute of cook time, add Nan's special seasoning and toss to coat. Transfer to a plate to rest.

TIP: Pounding the beef ensures that it's extra tender once cooked.

• While the steak is resting, combine a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then add mixed salad leaves, tomato and cucumber. Toss to combine.

• Slice spiced steak.
• Divide steak, veggie fries and garden salad between plates.
• Serve with mayonnaise.